          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Yield curves for photoprotons  with  energies  higher",
                " than 1.8  MeV  emitted  from nuclei 112Sn and 124Sn",
                " are measured from threshold up to 29  MeV  with  200",
                " keV step using semiconductor silicon detectors.  The",
                " (gamma,p)  reaction  cross  sections were calculated",
                " from the  yield curves by means of the Penfold-Leiss",
                " method. The cross section curve for 112Sn  increases",
                " appreciably starting from 13 MeV, reaching the value",
                " of about 17 mb at energy of about 18 MeV,  and has a",
                " number of  maxima  in  the  region 14 - 27 MeV.  The",
                " cross section for 124Sn is nonzero only at E >  19.5",
                " MeV and  has  a maxima at 20.7,  about 23,  and 25.5",
                " MeV. The  integral cross sections  of the  (gamma,p)",
                " reaction amount  to  129  (20) and 15 (3) mb*MeV for",
                " 112Sn and 124Sn, respectively. The obtained results",
                " are in  qualitative  agreement with the calculations",
                " based on the shell model with account of the isospin",
                " and residual interactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
